73
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:48,190
You two may be separated but I still envy you,

74
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:50,390
a female lawyer who never loses

75
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:53,390
and a private detective who always solves his cases, what a couple.

76
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,490
Oh no...

77
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:57,890
I'm just an worthless man who is ever so proud

78
00:05:57,890 --> 00:06:00,990
to be married to a grand lady.

79
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:02,190
You're right.

80
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:05,990
Then that must mean I'm a stupid woman

81
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:09,390
who's picked a woman chasing private detective, a low-life

82
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:11,390
who looks for the dirt in other people's lives as the man

83
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:13,990
to share her life with.

84
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:19,090
Good grief, how can you say that every time.

85
00:06:19,090 --> 00:06:21,290
Mr. Mouri solves a case,

86
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:24,990
you cut out the article in the newspaper and put it in your scrapbook.

87
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:26,490
No, I don't.

88
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:28,490
Dad does that too.

89
00:06:28,490 --> 00:06:31,290
Late at night, he sneaks

90
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:33,290
and reads all articles on the cases mom is working on.

91
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:36,090
Right, dad?

92
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:37,790
Don't tell her, you idiot.

93
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:39,690
Come on now, here we are, all in Karuizawa.

94
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:42,990
Let's just call a truce for tonight and have a good time.

95
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:49,190
Well, if Eri doesn't object, I'll oblige.

96
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:53,490
I don't mind... not one bit.

97
00:06:54,590 --> 00:06:56,090
What is this? What's going on?

98
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:57,690
Could it be? They're still in love?

99
00:06:58,690 --> 00:07:00,290
No way.

100
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:12,390
I'd like to hear Ritsuko's sweet voice pleading my case in court too.

101
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:14,190
Mr. Mouri.

102
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:19,890
I'm kidding.

103
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:21,490
Dad!

104
00:07:21,490 --> 00:07:25,490
Ritsuko, your little hands are so cute.

105
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:27,790
You're my type.

106
00:07:28,790 --> 00:07:31,390
From this to that.

107
00:07:32,590 --> 00:07:34,290
Mom, wait!

108
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,990
What a drunkard.

109
00:07:39,590 --> 00:07:41,090
Wait a minute.

110
00:07:42,090 --> 00:07:46,890
Mom, you know that dad always gets like that when he's drunk.

111
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:50,390
Besides, you were with a man today yourself.

112
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:52,490
You looked so happy, choosing that tie.

113
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:55,390
You're right.

114
00:07:55,390 --> 00:07:57,690
I shouldn't have bought this thing.

115
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:01,290
I let my guard down for one moment

116
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:03,890
and now I'm so mad, I think I might explode.

117
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:07,090
I don't believe it, you mean that tie's...

118
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:08,890
Yes, that's right.

119
00:08:08,890 --> 00:08:11,990
Tomorrow's our wedding anniversary.

120
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:13,690
I felt sorry for you

121
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:15,990
and I thought maybe it was time for me to forgive him

122
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:18,590
so I figured I'd give him a present

123
00:08:18,590 --> 00:08:20,790
but I'm glad I didn't.

124
00:08:23,290 --> 00:08:24,690
Then I'll take that!

125
00:08:24,690 --> 00:08:25,690
Hey, wait...

126
00:08:27,490 --> 00:08:29,690
I'll give it to him for you!

127
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:31,790
No, come right back here!

128
00:08:39,490 --> 00:08:42,390
I think I'll give it to him myself.

129
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:45,890
Good grief.

130
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:50,890
Did everybody leave?

131
00:08:50,890 --> 00:08:52,290
Dad too?

132
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:56,290
He said he was going back to the room to sleep because he felt drunk...

133
00:08:56,290 --> 00:08:57,790
Mom.

134
00:08:57,790 --> 00:09:00,890
I think dad's in his room. Good luck.

135
00:09:00,890 --> 00:09:02,790
All right.

136
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:14,990
Yes.

137
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:16,890
Ms. Kisaki.

138
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,690
I know it's late and I apologize

139
00:09:18,690 --> 00:09:20,790
but is my husband here?

140
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:23,690
No, he's not, why?

141
00:09:23,690 --> 00:09:25,390
I see.

142
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:27,290
Is something wrong?

143
00:09:27,290 --> 00:09:29,190
I can't find dad,

144
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:33,590
he's not in our room or in the other 3 people's rooms.

145
00:09:33,590 --> 00:09:37,690
Maybe he's wandering around outside,

146
00:09:37,690 --> 00:09:40,790
he likes to feel the night air.

147
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:43,190
I'm sorry we disturbed you,

148
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:44,890
we'll go look outside.

149
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,290
Excuse us.

150
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:50,090
Let's go find him.

151
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:51,390
Yes, let's go.

152
00:09:58,090 --> 00:10:00,190
Forgive me, Ms. Kisaki,

153
00:10:00,190 --> 00:10:02,290
but I've finally discovered

154
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:05,290
that I'll never be like you, no matter how hard I try.

155
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:09,390
The only way I can ever rise above you...

156
00:10:11,190 --> 00:10:14,190
is you've got to fall a few notches.

157
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,490
If you thought there was something

158
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:27,790
between your beloved husband here and me,

159
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,590
your ability to think clearly would be affected

160
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:31,290
and your work would suffer,

161
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:34,190
then you'd be forced to relinquish your title as number one to me.

162
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:36,090
Ritsuko Usui.

163
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:41,490
Good grief, are they back again?

164
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:44,290
How persistent.

165
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:50,390
What can I do for you?

166
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:58,990
Mr. Mouri's still not back?

167
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:00,790
Are you sure about that?

168
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:02,190
Yes.

169
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:03,390
We've looked everywhere, the hotel grounds,

170
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:06,690
the roof, the stairways, everywhere.

171
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:10,590
It's already 2 am.

172
00:11:10,590 --> 00:11:12,490
That's strange.

173
00:11:12,490 --> 00:11:13,990
He left with Miss Usui

174
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:17,290
because he said they were staying on the same floor.

175
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:18,990
I see.

176
00:11:18,990 --> 00:11:21,090
So that leaves...

177
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:26,990
Ritsuko's room is the only one we haven't checked.

178
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:30,690
This wasn't here when we came here earlier.

179
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:31,890
Earlier?

180
00:11:31,890 --> 00:11:33,590
We came here earlier to ask

181
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:35,290
but she said he wasn't with her.

182
00:11:35,290 --> 00:11:36,890
Of course he wouldn't be.

183
00:11:36,890 --> 00:11:40,490
I doubt those two would.

184
00:11:40,490 --> 00:11:42,790
Mom, what are you doing?

185
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:44,190
Be quiet.

186
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:53,090
I don't believe it.

187
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:56,490
There's no mistake. That's his cellular phone.

188
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:58,090
It can't be.

189
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:00,190
Mikasa, I hate to ask but could you go to the front desk

190
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:01,790
and borrow their master key?

191
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:02,790
You bet.

192
00:12:09,890 --> 00:12:11,490
-Please. -Thank you.

193
00:12:12,490 --> 00:12:14,690
Look, the door chain's on.

194
00:12:19,690 --> 00:12:21,190
What's the matter?

195
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:25,190
Hey, that's...

196
00:12:25,190 --> 00:12:26,590
Isn't that Ritsuko?

197
00:12:28,690 --> 00:12:31,290
Bell boy. Get the chain cutter, quick.

198
00:12:34,290 --> 00:12:35,690
Stand back.

199
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:38,290
There's no time to waste.

200
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:41,690
Ritsuko.

201
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:43,790
Ritsuko.

202
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:48,990
Come on. What's wrong? Wake up.

203
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:49,990
Stop.

204
00:12:52,990 --> 00:12:55,190
I don't feel a pulse.

205
00:12:55,190 --> 00:12:56,690
That's impossible.

206
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:58,390
What happened?

207
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:02,590
Boy, what's all the racket about?

208
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:05,790
What's going on here?

209
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:09,190
-Dad? -Kogoro.

210
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:29,880
Why are you here?

211
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,980
The chain was on the door.

212
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:36,480
Ritsuko's body was on the floor

213
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:40,980
and only one other person was in this locked room.

214
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:46,780
-Hey, now... What's going on here? -Don't step on that.

215
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:49,680
That telephone cord on the floor is probably the weapon.

216
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:52,580
-Murder weapon? -Look, over there.

217
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:56,280
See the thin marking around her neck?

218
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,380
I see.

219
00:13:57,380 --> 00:14:01,380
You're saying she was strangled with the telephone cord.

220
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:04,580
Hey. Why's Miss Usui lying on the...

221
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,380
Did you say strangled?

222
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:11,180
By who?

223
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,880
You're the one who could've done it.

224
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,780
Why'd you kill her?

225
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:17,380
Now just hold on.

226
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:19,380
I'm sure this is some kind of mistake.

227
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:21,880
My father would never kill anyone,

228
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:24,280
would he, mom?

229
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:28,080
Penal code 499...

230
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,380
A person charged with murder will be sentenced

231
00:14:30,380 --> 00:14:34,880
to life or a minimum sentence of three years or...

232
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:36,180
the death penalty.

233
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:37,280
What?

234
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:39,080
Mom?

235
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,680
Ran. Why are you standing around?

236
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,880
Call the police at once.

237
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,880
She's got to be kidding.

238
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:52,280
Let me get this straight.

239
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:54,980
Your husband was missing,

240
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,780
you thought he might be in this room

241
00:14:56,780 --> 00:14:59,580
so you called him on his cellular

242
00:14:59,580 --> 00:15:00,680
and as you suspected,

243
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:04,780
you heard his cellular ringing in this room.

244
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:07,880
When you used the master key to unlock the door,

245
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:10,380
you found the chain was on

246
00:15:10,380 --> 00:15:11,980
and you could see the victim lying on the floor

247
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:14,880
in the space between the door.

248
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,580
"Misao Yamamura" -When you broke down the door and entered the room,

249
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:20,580
"Gunma Prefecture Police Officer" -you found the victim was already dead,

250
00:15:20,580 --> 00:15:24,180
and your husband was asleep on this bed, right?

251
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:25,880
Yes.

252
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,380
Then I'm sorry to tell you this

253
00:15:27,380 --> 00:15:29,980
but your husband is the murderer.

254
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:32,380
That's not fair!

255
00:15:32,380 --> 00:15:35,880
Just wait a minute. Dad, don't just stand there, say something.

256
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,780
Hey? I know you.

257
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:40,680
Aren't you Kogoro Mouri?

258
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:43,080
-Yes. -I'm in luck.

259
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:47,680
With a famous private detective like you on the scene,

260
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,880
this case's good as solved.

261
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:52,080
Why don't you tell me your thoughts regarding this murder?

262
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,780
Yes, dear.

263
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:58,180
Why don't you tell him all about what happened here

264
00:15:58,180 --> 00:16:02,180
while you were snoring up a storm, Mr. Famous Private Detective?

265
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:06,580
He's your husband? You're married to Kogoro Mouri?

266
00:16:06,580 --> 00:16:08,880
But, then, that means...

267
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:11,580
Then you're the murderer?

268
